title: Security lapse: HC orders probe of Amritsar incident by Haryana cadre IPS officer
title_detail: {'type': 'text/plain', 'language': 'en-IN', 'base': 'https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/rssfeeds/-2128816762.cms', 'value': 'Security lapse: HC orders probe of Amritsar incident by Haryana cadre IPS officer'}
summary: The Punjab and Haryana High Court has appointed IPS officer Manisha Chaudhary to investigate the suicide incident outside the Golden Temple involving an ASI's pistol. Chaudhary, currently AIG in Haryana police, will conduct a fair and impartial probe, submitting weekly reports. The court clarified its earlier comments on Punjab police's security lapse.

title: Breather for govt, farmers: Arhtiyas to participate in Basmati purchase
title_detail: {'type': 'text/plain', 'language': 'en-IN', 'base': 'https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/rssfeeds/-2128816762.cms', 'value': 'Breather for govt, farmers: Arhtiyas to participate in Basmati purchase'}
summary: In a partial relief for Punjab, commission agents, or arhtiyas, will continue to buy Basmati rice and cotton, though they are still boycotting paddy procurement by state agencies. This decision followed a meeting with state officials. Mandi laborers remain on strike but will reassess their position on Friday, demanding better pay and conditions.
